==Gothic==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*guma-'', from Indo-European ''*g'hﾉ冦o-, g'homo-''. Germanic cognates include Old Saxon [[gumo]], Old High German [[gumo]], Old Norse [[gumi]] (Norwegian [[gume]]), Old English [[guma]]. The IE root is also the source of Latin [[homo]], Baltic ''*ﾅｾmo-'' (Lithuanian [[ﾅｾmogus|ﾅｾmﾅ紅ﾃｹs]]).

